<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>She never fails to impress with her striking fashion ensembles.</p>

<p>And Paris Hilton was sure to turn up the heat as she rocked a pink cut-out leotard during Rihanna's Savage x Fenty show on Thursday.</p>

<p>The hotel heiress, 39, put on a sultry display as she flaunted her sensational figure in the slinky lingerie and a pair of bright pink fishnet tights.</p>

<p>Wow! Paris Hilton looked sensational as she struck a sultry pose in a cut-out leotard and pink fishnet tights during Rihanna's Savage x Fenty show on Thursday</p>

<p>Paris exuded confidence at the event, making sure to work all of her angles as she showed off the eye-catching look.</p>

<p>She styled her locks into an enormous 80s-inspired hair do, letting her blonde tresses cascade over her shoulders.</p>

<p>The beauty also rocked a full face of makeup, including a slick of pink lipstick, before adding some Noughties-esque sunglasses to her ensemble.</p>

<p>Never one to forgo a chance to add some sparkle, Paris jazzed up her outfit with dazzling silver jewellery and a shimmering detail on her heels.</p>

<p>Work it: The heiress flaunted her toned figure, flashing her taut midriff in the cut-out lingerie </p>

<p>As well as wowing in pink, Paris was also spotted posing up a storm in a black corset and semi-sheer mini skirt as she arrived at the show.</p>

<p>She kept with the fishnet theme for her second look, but went for a more classic pair of black knee-high stockings. </p>

<p>Also seen during the show-studded event were models Bella Hadid, Irina Shayk and Cara Delevingne who all impressed in a selection of lingerie.</p>

<p>Rihanna's Savage X Fenty show will be broadcast on Amazon Prime video on Friday, October 2. </p>

<p>Pose: Paris added matching pink lace gloves to her ensemble and posed for some snaps with Willow Smith, 19, during the star-studded event</p>

<p>Looking good: She also slipped into a a black corset with a semi-sheer skirt and fishnet stockings as she arrived at the event</p>

<p>Behind the scenes it seemed safety was the number one priority as the crew was spotted in masks and protective face shields.</p>

<p>Although it seemed some of the models weren't akin to the rules of social distancing as they posed together backstage. </p>

<p>Rihanna also told People that part of organising the show was ensured that all of the models were safe in the midst of the COVID-19 pandemic.</p>

<p>She said: 'It was a completely different process this year. We had to work around the challenges of COVID-19, keeping everyone safe and their health at the top of our list. It forced us to figure out new ways to produce a show. </p>

<p>Incredible: Rihanna wore a cut-out bra under a leather blazer at the Savage x Fenty press day at the Convention Center in LA on Wednesday</p>

<p>Getting ready: Meanwhile Bella was transformed into a fishnet clad vixen dressed in a skimpy black lingerie, with the help of three crew members in preparation for her fashionable display</p>

<p>Jaw-dropping: Cara Delevingne set pulses racing in a plunging black velvet bra with silver embroidery (left) while Irina Shayk paraded her amazing physique in a sheer black lace bra and sequinned shorts, teamed with a long silk robe</p>

<p>Eye-popping: Backed by shirtless and lace-clad dancers, Irina proved she could be the centre of attention in a sea of stunning models as she strutted down the runway</p>

<p>'We had to figure out ways to make this feel as visually enthusiastic as possible. I’m excited, and I’m proud of my team — we pulled it off."</p>

<p>Forbes revealed in 2019 that Rihanna — who's real name is Robyn Rihanna Fenty — is the richest female musical artist.</p>

<p>The Diamonds singer's $600 million net worth has eclipsed the fortunes earned by her peers Beyonce, Madonna and Celine Dion, according to the publication. </p>

<p>In addition to her fashion ventures, Rihanna dipped into the world of cosmetics in 2017 with Fenty Beauty, a company which accrued nearly $570m in revenue in 2018.</p>

<p>That's how it's done: Stepping into a green-lit room, Umbrella hitmaker Rihanna changed  her look for some striking leather hotpants, black gloves and an oversized statement top</p>
